You have problem in `publishResults` method.

As you have used `plistFull` to binding data in recyclerview. You have to add `filtered` data in this list.

**Replace this code**

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    @Override
                protected void publishResults(CharSequence constraint, FilterResults results) {
                    plistFull.clear();
                    plistFull.addAll((List) results.values);
                    notifyDataSetChanged();
                }

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;



But the problem is you will loss your actual data after replace `plistFull` with filtered data. 

If you have required this actual data again then you have store this actual list in some other list. You can use other list for that. 


**Use below code for that**
&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    public class PersonSearchResultAdapter extends RecyclerView.Adapter&lt;PersonSearchResultAdapter.MyViewHolder&gt; implements Filterable {

        private Context mContext;
        private List&lt;Person&gt; actualDataList = new ArrayList();
        private List&lt;Person&gt; plistFull = null;

        @Override
        public Filter getFilter() {
            return new Filter() {
                @Override
                protected FilterResults performFiltering(CharSequence constraint) {
                    List&lt;Person&gt; filteredList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
                    if (constraint == null | constraint.length() == 0) {
                        filteredList.addAll(plistFull);
                    }
                    else {
                        String filterPattern = constraint.toString().toLowerCase().trim();
                        for (Person p : plistFull) {
                            if (p.getName().toLowerCase().contains(filterPattern)) {
                                filteredList.add(p);
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    FilterResults results = new FilterResults();
                    results.values = filteredList;
                    return results;
                }

                @Override
                protected void publishResults(CharSequence constraint, FilterResults results) {
                    actualDataList = plistFull; // This will save your actual data list.
                    plistFull.clear();
                    plistFull.addAll((List) results.values);
                    notifyDataSetChanged();
                }
            };
        }
    }

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

